Always wonderful. We were coming home from Harrisburg and had planned to stop in Frederick for an early dinner. There was only one place to go, Sabor de Cuba. We sat outside under an umbrella on the street, behind barricades. A lively conversation was happening at the next table and it ended up being the co-owners, Mike and Sergio. We talked for quite awhile and discovered that a couple we sent there (Cuban) have become quite friendly with them. They were thrilled to meet the connection. We even took a picture of Mike and his daughter Giselle, who works there. It's a family affair.  Most of the recipes are Mike's grandmother's, who taught him to cook. We had the ham croquettes, the sizzling shrimp appetizer, and beef empanadas. It was perfect, especially with the habanero Margaritas. We took a Cuban sandwich and pan con lechon to go. Hugely recommended. Do yourself a favor. Just GO!

I've been to this place a bunch of times and the food and service is always amazing.  This last time, we showed up five minutes before closing (thought they closed at 10pm, but they close at 8:30pm M-Th), and they still sat us.  In fact, they seemed happy to.  One of the owners was conversing with an older couple about the Cuban culture and history.  We ordered the Bistec Enchilada, Cubano, y Sándwich de Pollo Especial which was marinated chicken ground and made into a patty with minced onions, bell peppers, jalapeños and spices, dressed with avocado spread.  Aimee, our waitress, said she was planning on taking one home herself after her shift because they are just that good.  We weren't disappointed in a single thing.  Even though they closed at 8:30pm, we were sat and served and ate and got our check at 9pm.  Our waitress continued talking with us, in no apparent rush.  When we are about to leave, we got into a conversation with the owner talking about how much we love the food and enjoy coming to Sabor de Cuba.  He was telling us how many of the recipes were family recipes, handed down from generations, tweaked by each one.  All in all, we had a great time, as always, and plan on coming back.
